Does $\blueD{(9 \times 3) \times 3}=\purpleC{9 \times 9}?$

$
\begin{align}
\blueD{(9 \times 3) \times 3} &\stackrel{?}{=}  \purpleC{9 \times 9}
\\\\
\blueD{9 \times (3 \times 3)} &\stackrel{?}{=}  \purpleC{9 \times 9} &&\text{Associative property of multiplication}\\\\
\blueD{9 \times 9} &=  \purpleC{9 \times 9}
 \end{align}$

Yes, $\blueD{(9 \times 3) \times 3}$ is equivalent to $\purpleC{9 \times 9}$.
